        <div class="comment_date"><a href="http://www.engadget.com/profile/291895/"><!-- (Unverified) --> (Unverified)</a> Posted <a href="./comments/2000092/">Aug 29th 2006 8:07PM</a></div>
		<span class="cmt_label label_level2" ><div class="comment_rank neutral">Neutral</div></span>
		<div class="clear"></div>
		<div class="comment_text"><p class="cmt_contents">Seems like a waste of projector pixels.  While some HDTV projectors are actually 16:9, most projectors people use are still 4:3.  With a screen like that, you are looking at using only about 2/3 of your projector's pixels to make an image.  Why not make a 4:3 screen, then show movies in 2.4:1 or whatever inside of that.  Same size image for movies, plus you can use it for games and TV.  </p></div>
	</div>
