		<div class="clear"></div>
		<div class="comment_text"><p class="cmt_contents">You don't necessarily have to use the expensive goo paint.  Of course, it is best, but if you're just looking for a decent screen, a cheap can of flat white primer paint works just fine.  With the brightness and contrast ratio of most projectors now days, the image is just fine for the average user.  I've used it in two home theaters now with great success.  The added bonus:  when your three-year-old decides to walk up and shake hands with Barney by touching the screen with his chocolate-covered hands, a quick job with the roller and you're good to go again.  (Try that with your fabric screen Engadget!).  </p></div>
